# Project Rules — Beanstalk Coffee v3

## Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router, `src/` directory)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 (via `@tailwindcss/postcss`)
- **Animation**: `@react-three/fiber` for 3D rendering, `@react-three/drei` for helpers, `framer-motion-3d` for scroll mapping.
- **State**: Zustand — BusyMeter widget state

## Code Standards
- Components < 150 lines. Modular, focused, reusable.
- Semantic HTML (`<section>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`) for the UI layer positioned over the Canvas.
- All 3D rendering MUST happen within the `<Canvas>` component. Do not use DOM elements for the cup or particles.
- `CoffeeCup3D.tsx` should use procedural Three.js `<cylinderGeometry>` to construct a cup model.
- CSS `backdrop-blur` should be used heavily to ensure the 3D layer is visible underneath content.

## File Structure
```
src/
  app/
    layout.tsx       — Root layout, Google Fonts, metadata
    page.tsx         — Assembles all sections. Canvas sits behind the HTML wrapper.
    globals.css      — Tailwind + premium theme tokens
  components/
    Scene3D.tsx      — The React Three Fiber <Canvas> environment
    CoffeeCup3D.tsx  — The procedural 3D model with scroll-linked translation/rotation
    CoffeeParticles3D.tsx — 3D floating geometries scattered near the path
    Hero.tsx         — HTML Typographic hero + BusyMeter widget
    BusyMeter.tsx    — Zustand-powered real-time capacity indicator
    TheVibe.tsx      — About section with glassmorphism overlays
    Menu.tsx         — 100% veg menu CSS grid + 3D tilt + steam animation
    SocialProof.tsx  — Rating badge (4.5★) + testimonial cards
    Footer.tsx       — Dark footer, address, hours
    QuickOrderFAB.tsx — localStorage-aware floating order button
  store/
    vibesStore.ts    — Zustand store for busy meter state
```

## Forbidden
- No `any` types
- No inline `style` that duplicates a Tailwind class
- No video elements in the hero
- No placeholder/stock images
